1
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:05,920
River?

2
00:00:06,440 --> 00:00:08,080
Follow that ship!

3
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:12,440
Has Dr Song explained
what we're dealing with?

4
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:13,600
AMY: Doctor...

5
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:15,480
what's it going to do to me?

6
00:00:15,560 --> 00:00:18,160
Amy, not the eyes, look at the Angel,
but don't look at the eyes.

7
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:22,920
OCTAVIAN: The Angel, as far as we know,
is still trapped in the ship -

8
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,560
our mission is to get inside
and neutralise it.

9
00:00:25,680 --> 00:00:29,480
DOCTOR: Don't you see? All that radiation
spilling out, the drive burn.

10
00:00:29,560 --> 00:00:30,560
The crash of the Byzantium
wasn't an accident -

11
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:33,480
it was a rescue mission for the Angels.
We're in the middle of an army.

12
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:35,640
The statues are advancing
on all sides.

13
00:00:35,760 --> 00:00:37,560
RIVER: There's no way up, no way back,
no way out.

14
00:00:37,640 --> 00:00:40,680
I'm about to do something
incredibly stupid and dangerous.

15
00:00:40,760 --> 00:00:42,320
When I do, jump.

16
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:43,720
- On my signal.
- What signal?

17
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:44,960
You won't miss it.

18
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:23,000
Up! Look up!

19
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:25,680
- You OK?
- What happened?

20
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:28,560
- We jumped.
- Jumped where?

21
00:01:28,640 --> 00:01:30,280
Up, up, look up!

22
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:33,280
- Where are we?
- RIVER: Exactly where we were.

23
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:34,480
- No, we're not.
- Move your feet!

24
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:38,760
Doctor, what am I looking at? Explain.

25
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:40,120
Oh, come on, Amy, think!

26
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,760
The ship crashed
with the power still on, yeah?

27
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:44,320
So what else is still on?

28
00:01:53,520 --> 00:01:56,560
The artificial gravity.
One good jump, and up we fell.

29
00:01:56,640 --> 00:02:00,320
Shot out the grav-globe to give us
an updraught, and here we are!

30
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:04,480
Doctor...the statues,
they look more like Angels now.

31
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,760
DOCTOR: They're feeding
on the radiation from the wreckage,

32
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,880
draining all the power from the ship,
restoring themselves.

33
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:10,640
Within an hour, they'll be an army.

34
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:17,280
They're taking out the lights.
Look at them, look at the Angels.

35
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:23,000
- Into the ship now - quickly, all of you!
- But how?

36
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,640
Doctor!

37
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:28,080
It's just a corridor,

38
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:31,280
the gravity orientates to the floor.

39
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:32,440
Now, in here, all of you,

40
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,960
don't take your eyes off the Angels -
move, move, move!

41
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:37,280
OCTAVIAN: OK, men, go, go, go!

42
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:43,560
The Angels...presumably
they can jump up too?

43
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:45,800
DOCTOR: They're here...now.

44
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:49,920
- In the dark, we're finished. Run!
- This whole place is a death trap!

45
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,320
No, it's a time bomb. Well,
it's a death trap and a time bomb.

46
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:55,400
And now it's a dead end.
Nobody panic.

47
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,960
Oh, just me, then.

48
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:01,120
- What's through here?
- Secondary Flight Deck.

49
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:04,520
OK, so we've basically run up
the inside of a chimney, yeah?

50
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:06,880
- So what if the gravity fails?
- I've thought about that.

51
00:03:06,960 --> 00:03:07,920
And?

52
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,680
And we'll all plunge to our deaths.
See, I've thought about it.

53
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:12,600
Ah, the security protocols are still live.
There's no way to override them,

54
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:13,960
- it's impossible.
- How impossible?

55
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:15,720
Two minutes.

56
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:20,400
OCTAVIAN: The hull is breached,
and the power's failing.

57
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:25,760
CLERIC: Sir, incoming!
AMY: Doctor, lights!

58
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:36,720
OCTAVIAN: Clerics, keep watching them.

59
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:40,000
DOCTOR: And don't look at their eyes -
anywhere else, not the eyes.

60
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:43,880
I've isolated the lighting grid -
they can't drain the power now.

61
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:45,160
OCTAVIAN: Good work, Doctor.

62
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:47,040
Yes, good, good, good. Good in many ways.
Good you like it so far...

63
00:03:47,120 --> 00:03:48,080
So far?!

64
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,960
Well, there's only one way
to open this door.

65
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:52,440
I guess I'll need to route
all the power in this section

66
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:54,520
- through the door control.
- Good, fine, do it.

67
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:57,640
Including the lights. All of them.
I'L need to turn out the lights.

68
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:03,360
- OCTAVIAN: How long for?
- Fraction of a second, maybe longer.

69
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:04,720
- Maybe quite a bit longer.
- Maybe?

70
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,920
I'm guessing. We're being attacked
by statues in a crashed ship -

71
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:07,960
there isn't a manual for this!

72
00:04:08,040 --> 00:04:10,400
Doctor, we lost the torches,
we'll be in total darkness.

73
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:13,680
No other way. Bishop...

74
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:17,120
Dr Song, I've lost good clerics today.
You trust this man?

75
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:21,520
- I absolutely trust him.
- He's not some kind of madman, then?

76
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,160
I absolutely trust him.

77
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,760
Excuse me.

78
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:29,040
I'm taking your word, because you're
the only one who can manage this guy.

79
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:31,720
But that only works so long
as he doesn't know who you are.

80
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:35,600
You cost me any more men,
and I might just tell him. Understood?

81
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:38,480
Understood.

82
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:42,920
- OK, Doctor, we've got your back.
- Bless you, Bishop.

83
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:46,360
Combat distance, ten feet. As soon as
the lights go down, continuous fire.

84
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:50,120
Full spread over the hostiles. Do not stop
firing while the lights are out.

85
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,360
Shotgun protocol -
we don't have bullets to waste.

86
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:55,120
DOCTOR: Amy, when the lights go down,
the wheel should release.

87
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,760
- Spin it clockwise, four turns.
- Ten.

88
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:58,480
No, four, four turns.

89
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,720
Yeah, four, I heard you.

90
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:01,680
Ready!

91
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:06,080
On my count, then.

92
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:09,440
God be with us all.

93
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:13,920
Three...two...one...

94
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,520
fire!

95
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,120
Turn!

96
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:25,640
AMY: It's opening, it's working.

97
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:28,280
OCTAVIAN: Fall back!

98
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:46,120
- RIVER: Doctor, quickly.
- AMY: Doctor!

99
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:56,880
Doctor!

100
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:03,320
AMY: What are you doing?

101
00:06:03,400 --> 00:06:06,920
Magnetised the door.
Nothing could turn that wheel now.

102
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Yeah?

103
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:15,600
- Dear God!
- Ah, now you're getting it!

104
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:18,400
You've bought us time, though,
that's good, I am good with time.

105
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,160
Doctor!

106
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,400
Seal that door, seal it now!

107
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:32,760
- We're surrounded.
- Seal it, seal that door.

108
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:37,600
- Doctor, how long have we got?
- Five minutes, max.

109
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,120
- Nine.
- Five.

110
00:06:39,200 --> 00:06:40,320
Five, right, yeah.

111
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:42,160
- Why did you say nine?
- I didn't.

112
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:46,240
- We need another way out of here.
- There isn't one.

113
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,440
Yeah, there is, course there is.

114
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:50,320
This is a galaxy class ship,
goes for years between planet-falls.

115
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,920
So what do they need?

116
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:55,080
- Of course.
- "Of course"” what? What do they need?

117
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:56,480
OCTAVIAN: Can we get in there?

118
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:59,720
Well, it's a sealed unit, but they
must have installed it somehow.

119
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:02,480
This whole wall should slide up.

120
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:06,200
There's clamps, release the clamps!

121
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,200
What's through there?
What do they need?

122
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:11,680
They need to breathe.

123
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:25,920
But that's...

124
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:30,520
That's a...

125
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:33,400
- RIVER: It's an oxygen factory.
- It's a forest.

126
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:36,760
RIVER: Yeah, it's a forest,
it's an oxygen factory.

127
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:39,040
DOCTOR: And if we're lucky,
an escape route.

128
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:44,840
- Eight!
- RIVER: What did you say?

129
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:48,080
- Nothing.
- Is there another exit?

130
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:51,040
Scan the architecture -
we don't have time to get lost in there.

131
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:54,920
On it! Stay where you are
until I've checked the rad levels.

132
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,800
But trees? On a spaceship?!

133
00:07:57,880 --> 00:08:01,520
Oh, more than trees, way better
than trees. You're going to love this.

134
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:05,400
Tree Borgs...

135
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:09,160
trees plus technology.

136
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:11,920
Branches become cables,
become sensors on the hull,

137
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:15,440
a forest sucking in starlight,
breathing out air.

138
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:17,560
It even rains.
There's a whole mini-climate.

139
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,840
This vault is an ecopod running
right through the heart of the ship.

140
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:22,360
A forest in a bottle
on a spaceship in a maze.

141
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:25,680
- Have I impressed you yet, Amy Pond?
- Seven.

142
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:28,760
- Seven?
- Sorry, what?

143
00:08:28,840 --> 00:08:30,560
You said seven.

144
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:32,400
- No, I didn't.
- Yes, you did.

145
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:35,760
OCTAVIAN: Doctor, there's an exit, far end
of the ship, into the Primary Flight Deck.

146
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:38,160
- Good. That's where we need to go.
- Plotting a safe path now.

147
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:39,400
Quick as you like!

148
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:43,720
ANGEL BOB: Doctor?
Excuse me. Hello, Doctor?

149
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:45,840
Angel Bob here, sir.

150
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:51,400
Ah, there you are, Angel Bob.
How's life? Sorry, bad subject.

151
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:53,720
The Angels are wondering
what you hope to achieve.

152
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,920
Achieve? We're not achieving anything.
We're just hanging.

153
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:59,480
It's nice in here - consoles, comfy
chairs, a forest. How's things with you?

154
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:01,240
The Angels are feasting, sir.

155
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:05,480
Soon we'll be able to absorb
enough power to consume this vessel,

156
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:08,720
this world,
and all the stars and worlds beyond.

157
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:11,080
Well, we've got comfy chairs,
did I mention?

158
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:12,840
We have no need of comfy chairs.

159
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:15,080
I made him say "comfy chairs"!

160
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:17,760
(LAUGHS) Six.

161
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:20,680
OK, Bob, enough chat. Here's what I want
to know. What have you done to Amy?

162
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:24,160
- There's something in her eye.
- What's in her eye?

163
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,800
- We are.
- What's he talking about?

164
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:27,680
Doctor, I'm five.

165
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:33,040
I mean, five.

166
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:37,320
Fine! I'm fine.

167
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:38,520
You're counting.

168
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:41,600
- Counting?
- You're counting down. From ten.

169
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,440
- You have been for a couple of minutes.
- Why?

170
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:45,840
- I don't know.
- Well, counting down to what?

171
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:48,640
I don't know.

172
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,960
We shall take her.
We shall take all of you.

173
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:53,600
We shall have dominion
over all time and space.

174
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:54,920
Get a life, Bob.

175
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,800
Oops, sorry again!

176
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:59,760
There's power on this ship,
but nowhere near that much.

177
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,840
With respect, sir,

178
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:04,080
there's more power on this ship
than you yet understand.

179
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:07,320
- (SCREECHING)
- What is that? Dear God, what is it?

180
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:10,960
They're back.

181
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:13,760
It's hard to put it in your terms,
Dr Song,

182
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:16,200
but as best as I understand it

183
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:18,240
the Angels are laughing.

184
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:20,720
Laughing?

185
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,720
Because you haven't noticed yet, sir.

186
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,680
The Doctor in the TARDIS hasn't noticed.

187
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:28,880
- Doctor...
- No, wait, there's something I've...

188
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:35,200
...missed.

189
00:10:39,040 --> 00:10:42,280
That's...that's like
the crack from my bedroom wall

190
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:44,080
- from when I was a little girl.
- Yes.

191
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:49,640
Two parts of space and time
that should never have touched.

192
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,520
OK, enough, we're moving out!

193
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,520
- Agreed. Doctor?
- Yeah. Fine!

194
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,160
- What are you doing?
- Right with you.

195
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:03,760
- We're not leaving without you!
- Oh, yes, you are. Bishop?

196
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:06,760
- Miss Pond, Dr Song, now!
- AMY: Doctor, come on!

197
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:09,880
So, what are you?

198
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:12,800
Oh, that's bad.

199
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:15,120
Ah, that's extremely very not good.

200
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:28,680
Do...not...blink.

201
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:35,600
Ah...

202
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:38,160
Argh!

203
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:52,640
Amy?

204
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,760
Amy, what's wrong?

205
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,440
Why am I not dead, then?

206
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:06,880
Good and not so good.

207
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:12,040
Oh, this isn't even a little bit good.
I mean, is that it?

208
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:14,400
Is that the power
that brought you here?

209
00:12:14,520 --> 00:12:16,360
That's pure time energy,
you can't feed on that, that's not power,

210
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:18,040
that's the fire
at the end of the universe.

211
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:21,200
- And I'lll tell you something else...
- ( RUMBLING)

212
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:24,240
Never let me talk!

213
00:12:27,760 --> 00:12:30,320
- Amy, what's wrong?
- Four.

214
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:42,440
Med-scanner, now!

215
00:12:44,880 --> 00:12:48,360
Dr Song, we can't stay here -
we've got to keep moving.

216
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:49,920
We wait for the Doctor.

217
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:53,840
Our mission
is to make this wreckage safe

218
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:56,640
and neutralise the Angels.
Until that is achieved...

219
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:58,960
Father Octavian,
when the Doctor's in the room,

220
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:01,200
your one and only mission
is to keep him alive long enough

221
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:04,760
to get everyone else home.
And trust me, it's not easy.

222
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:07,440
Now, if he's dead back there,
I'LL never forgive myself,

223
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:11,080
and if he's alive,
I'LL never forgive him.

224
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:13,840
And, Doctor, you're standing
right behind me, aren't you?

225
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:15,680
Oh, yeah.

226
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:18,560
- I hate you!
- You don't.

227
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:19,800
Bishop, the Angels are in the forest.

228
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:21,880
OCTAVIAN: We need visual contact
on every line of approach.

229
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:23,040
How did you get past them?

230
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:25,160
I found a crack in the wall and told them
it was the end of the universe.

231
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,760
What was it?

232
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:29,320
The end of the universe.
Let's have a look, then.

233
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:32,000
- So what's wrong with me?
- RIVER: Nothing, you're fine.

234
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:34,520
- Everything, you're dying.
- Doctor!

235
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:38,280
Yes, you're right, if we lie to her,
she'll get all better(!) Right, Amy.

236
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:40,240
Amy, Amy,
what's the matter with Amelia?

237
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,720
Something's in her eye -
what does that mean?

238
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:42,960
- Does it mean anything?
- Doctor...

239
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:44,040
- Busy!
- Scared!

240
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:46,640
- Course, you're dying, shut up!
- OK, let him think.

241
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:49,000
What happened?

242
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:51,600
She stared at the Angel, she looked into
the eyes of an Angel for too long...

243
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:53,280
Sir! Angel, incoming!

244
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:56,880
And here.

245
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:01,520
Keep visual contact -
do not let it move!

246
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,880
Come on, come on, come on,
wakey, wakey!

247
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:07,000
She watched an Angel climb out
of the screen,

248
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:10,600
- she stared at the Angel, and, and...
- The image of an Angel ls an Angel.

249
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:12,320
A living mental image
in a living human mind.

250
00:14:12,400 --> 00:14:15,200
We stare at them to stop them
getting closer, we don't even blink,

251
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:16,840
and that is exactly what they want,

252
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:19,120
cos as long as our eyes are open,
they can climb inside.

253
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:21,120
There's an Angel in her mind!

254
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:23,760
Three.

255
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:28,800
Doctor, it's coming, I can feel it.
I'm going to die!

256
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:32,000
Please just shut up, I'm thinking.
Now counting, what's that about?

257
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:34,240
Bob, why are they making her count?

258
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:37,000
- To make her afraid, sir.
- OK, but why, what for?

259
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:39,120
For fun, sir.

260
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:42,240
Oh...argh!

261
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:48,520
Doctor, what's happening to me?
Explain!

262
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:51,560
Inside your head, in the vision centres
of your brain, there's an Angel.

263
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:54,120
It's like there's a screen,
a virtual screen inside your mind,

264
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:56,520
and the Angel is climbing out of it
and it's coming...

265
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:58,120
to shut you off.

266
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:00,360
Then what I do?

267
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:03,440
If it was a real screen, what would we do?
We'd pull the plug, kill the power.

268
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:04,480
But we can't just knock her out -

269
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:06,480
- the Angel would just take over!
- Then what? Quickly!

270
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:08,800
We've got to shut down
the vision centres of her brain,

271
00:15:08,880 --> 00:15:12,600
- pull the plug, starve the Angel.
- Doctor, she's got seconds.

272
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:14,040
How would you starve your lungs?

273
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:16,240
- I'd stop breathing.
- Amy, close your eyes!

274
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:18,680
No, no, I don't want to.

275
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:21,560
Good, cos that's not you,
that's the Angel inside you, it's afraid!

276
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:22,800
Do it! Close your eyes!

277
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:31,400
(BEEPING)

278
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:33,480
She's normalising.

279
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:35,560
(SIGHS)

280
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:39,200
You did it! You did it!

281
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:45,760
Sir? Two more incoming.

282
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:49,520
Three more over here.

283
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:51,640
Still weak, dangerous to move her.

284
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:54,560
- So can I open my eyes now?
- Amy, listen to me.

285
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:57,720
If you open your eyes now
for more than a second, you will die.

286
00:15:57,800 --> 00:15:59,640
The Angel is still inside you.

287
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:04,160
We haven't stopped it -
we've just sort of...paused it.

288
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:08,000
You've used up your countdown.
You cannot open your eyes.

289
00:16:08,080 --> 00:16:10,840
Doctor, we're too exposed here,
we have to move on.

290
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:13,160
We're too exposed everywhere,
and Amy can't move,

291
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,600
and anyway that's not the plan.

292
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:17,000
- RIVER: There's a plan?
- I don't know yet. I haven't finished.

293
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:20,000
Right! Father, you and your clerics
will stay here, look after Amy.

294
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,040
If anything happens to her,

295
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:24,600
I'LL hold every single one of you
personally responsible - twice.

296
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:25,720
River, you and me,

297
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:29,280
we're going to go and find
the Primary Flight Deck, which is...

298
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:32,760
...a quarter of a mile straight ahead,

299
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:34,400
and we'll stabilise the wreckage,
stop the Angels and cure Amy.

300
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:36,000
- How?
- I'll do a thing.

301
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,080
What thing?

302
00:16:37,160 --> 00:16:39,840
I don't know. It's a thing in progress,
respect the thing. Moving out!

303
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:43,440
Doctor, I'm coming with you.
My clerics will look after Miss Pond.

304
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:46,640
These are my best men, they'd lay down
their lives in her protection.

305
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:47,880
- I don't need you.
- I don't care.

306
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:50,880
- Where Dr Song goes, I go.
- What?

307
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:55,800
You two engaged or something?

308
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:58,960
Yes. In a manner of speaking.

309
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:02,680
Marco, you're in charge till I get back.

310
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:03,960
Sir!

311
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:07,640
Doctor...please, can't I come with you?

312
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:09,960
You'd slow us down, Miss Pond.

313
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:14,160
I don't want to sound selfish,
but you'd really speed me up.

314
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:17,320
You'll be safer here -
we can't protect you on the move.

315
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:20,160
I'll be back for you as soon as I can,
I promise.

316
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:22,720
- You always say that.
- I always come back.

317
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:27,400
Good luck, everyone. Behave,
do not let that girl open her eyes.

318
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:31,280
And keep watching the forest,
stop those Angels advancing.

319
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:34,440
Amy, later!
River, going to need your computer!

320
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,680
Yeah.

321
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:39,800
Later.

322
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:50,920
Amy, you need to start trusting me -
it's never been more important.

323
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,880
But you don't always
tell me the truth.

324
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:55,720
If I always told you the truth,
I wouldn't need you to trust me.

325
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:58,200
Doctor...

326
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:00,240
the crack in my wall...

327
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:01,880
how can it be here?

328
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,760
I don't know yet,
but I'm working it out.

329
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:06,720
Now, listen.

330
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,920
Remember what I told you
when you were seven?

331
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:12,800
- What did you tell me?
- No, no...

332
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:15,760
that's not the point.

333
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:19,120
You have to remember.

334
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:27,360
Remember what?

335
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:30,080
Doctor?

336
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:32,360
Doctor?

337
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:38,640
- What's that?
- Er, readings from a crack in a wall.

338
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:41,360
How can a crack in a wall
be the end of the universe?

339
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:43,240
I don't know, but here's what I think.
One day, there'll be a very big bang,

340
00:18:43,320 --> 00:18:46,920
so big every moment in history,
past and future, will crack.

341
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:48,560
Is that possible? How?

342
00:18:48,640 --> 00:18:51,920
How can you be engaged
in a manner of speaking?

343
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:54,440
Well...

344
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:57,000
Sucker for a man in uniform.

345
00:19:01,320 --> 00:19:04,040
Dr Song is in my personal custody.

346
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:07,920
I released her from the Stormcage
Containment Facility four days ago

347
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:09,560
and I am legally responsible for her

348
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:13,680
until she has accomplished
her mission and earned her pardon.

349
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:16,800
Just so we understand each other.

350
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:20,440
You were in Stormcage?

351
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:22,480
(BEEPING)

352
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:23,760
What? What is that?

353
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:27,840
The date, the date of the explosion,
where the crack begins.

354
00:19:27,920 --> 00:19:31,640
And for those of us who can't read
the base code of the universe?

355
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:35,120
Amy's time!

356
00:19:37,360 --> 00:19:40,600
So...what's happening?
Anything happening out there?

357
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,440
CLERIC: The Angels are still grouping.

358
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:52,360
Are you getting this too?

359
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:54,280
- The trees? Yeah.
- What's wrong with the trees?

360
00:19:54,360 --> 00:19:57,680
Here too, sir.
They're ripping the Tree Borgs apart.

361
00:19:57,760 --> 00:20:00,120
And here,
they're taking out the lights.

362
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:03,200
What is it, what's happening?
Tell me, I can't see.

363
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:06,360
It's the trees, ma'am.
The trees are going out.

364
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:15,120
It doesn't open it from here.

365
00:20:15,200 --> 00:20:17,960
But it's the Primary Flight Deck -

366
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:19,680
this has got to be a service hatch
or something.

367
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:22,120
Hurry up and open it -
time's running out.

368
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:25,240
What? What did you say? "Time's
running out” - is that what you said?

369
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:26,760
Yeah, I just meant...

370
00:20:26,840 --> 00:20:29,280
I know what you meant, hush!

371
00:20:29,360 --> 00:20:32,520
- But what if it could?
- What if what could?

372
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:35,720
- Time. What if time could run out?
- Got it!

373
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:40,240
- Angels advancing, sir.
- Over here, again.

374
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:45,440
Weapons primed, combat distance
five feet, wait for it!

375
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:47,920
What is it? What's happening?
Just tell me!

376
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,800
Keep your position and, ma'am,

377
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:53,080
keep your eyes shut! Wait!

378
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,440
The ship's not on fire, is it?

379
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:06,760
It can't be - the compressors
would have taken care of it.

380
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:14,320
Marco, the Angels have gone.

381
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,240
- Where'd they go?
- What, the Angels?

382
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:20,280
- This side's clear too, sir.
- AMY: The Angels have gone?

383
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:23,240
There's still movement out there,
but away from us now.

384
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:25,760
- It's like they're running.
- Running from what?

385
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:30,200
Phillip, Crispin,

386
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:32,040
need to get a closer look at that.

387
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:40,040
What are you all looking at?
What's there?

388
00:21:43,320 --> 00:21:46,000
Cracks...cracks in time,
time running out... No, couldn't be.

389
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:48,760
But how is a duck pond a duck pond
if there aren't any ducks?

390
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:51,080
And she didn't recognise the Daleks!

391
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:56,720
OK, time can shift, time can change,
time can be rewritten. Ah! Oh!

392
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:05,080
It's like...I don't know...
a curtain of energy, sort of shifting.

393
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:07,120
Makes you feel weird.

394
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:10,120
- Sick.
- And you think it scared the Angels?

395
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:12,240
What could scare those things?

396
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:14,520
- What are you doing?
- Point me at the light.

397
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:15,920
You can't open your eyes.

398
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:18,960
Can't open them for more than a second -
that's what the Doctor said.

399
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:21,200
Still got a bit of countdown left.

400
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:23,560
- Ma'am, you can't.
- I need to see it.

401
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:26,840
Am I looking the right way?
I have to be quick.

402
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:28,840
Very quick!

403
00:22:28,920 --> 00:22:31,040
OK.

404
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:40,800
It's the same shape!

405
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:42,280
It's the crack in my wall.

406
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:45,360
Close your eyes. Now!

407
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:48,280
It's following me!
How can it be following me?

408
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:56,480
- Are you OK?
- Yeah.

409
00:22:56,560 --> 00:22:58,040
It was the same shape.

410
00:22:58,120 --> 00:23:01,160
Marco, you want me
to get a closer look at that?

411
00:23:01,240 --> 00:23:03,600
Go for it.

412
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:06,280
- Don't get too close.
- Hang on, what about the other two?

413
00:23:06,360 --> 00:23:09,600
- Why not just wait until they're back?
- What other two?

414
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:11,640
The ones you sent before.

415
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:13,440
I didn't send anyone before.

416
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:16,160
You did, I heard you. Crispin and Phillip.

417
00:23:16,240 --> 00:23:18,280
Crispin and who?

418
00:23:21,520 --> 00:23:23,720
Dr Song, get through, now.

419
00:23:23,800 --> 00:23:26,120
Doctor?

420
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:30,880
Doctor?

421
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:33,920
Time can be urwritten.

422
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:36,520
Amy, there never was
a Crispin or a Phillip

423
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:40,120
- on this mission, I promise you.
- No, I heard you.

424
00:23:40,200 --> 00:23:43,000
Before you sent Pedro,
you sent Crispin and Phillip,

425
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:45,080
and now you can't
even remember them.

426
00:23:45,160 --> 00:23:46,840
Something happened,

427
00:23:46,920 --> 00:23:49,520
I don't know what,
and you don't even remember!

428
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:52,520
- Pedro?
- Yeah, before you sent Pedro.

429
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:55,160
Who's Pedro?

430
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:57,680
It's been happening all around me,
and I haven't even noticed!

431
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:59,120
Doctor, we have to move.

432
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:02,160
The CyberKing! A giant Cyberman
walks over all of Victorian London,

433
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:03,240
and no-one even remembers.

434
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:05,080
We have to move it!
The Angels could be here any second.

435
00:24:05,160 --> 00:24:07,840
Never mind the Angels -
there's worse here than Angels!

436
00:24:12,360 --> 00:24:14,120
I beg to differ, sir.

437
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:16,640
Let him go.

438
00:24:16,720 --> 00:24:20,760
Well, it can't let me go, sir,
not while you're looking at it.

439
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:22,240
I can't stop looking at it,
it'll kill you.

440
00:24:22,320 --> 00:24:26,520
It's going to kill me anyway. Think it
through. There's no way out of this.

441
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:29,160
- You have to leave me!
- Can't you wriggle out?

442
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:32,640
No, it's too tight. You have to leave me,
sir. There's nothing you can do.

443
00:24:32,720 --> 00:24:34,280
Something's happening!

444
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:37,080
Pedro was here a second ago,
and now you can't even remember him!

445
00:24:37,200 --> 00:24:40,640
There never was a Pedro -
there's only ever been the two of us here.

446
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:43,280
No, there were five of us -
why can't you remember?

447
00:24:43,360 --> 00:24:44,440
Listen, listen,

448
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:48,320
I need to get a closer look
at that...light, whatever it is.

449
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:50,520
Don't worry, I won't get too close.

450
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:52,920
No, you can't, you mustn't.

451
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:56,000
Here, spare communicator.

452
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:59,040
- I'll stay in touch the whole time.
- You won't.

453
00:24:59,120 --> 00:25:01,960
If you go back there, what happened
to the others will happen to you!

454
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:04,000
There weren't any others!

455
00:25:04,080 --> 00:25:06,720
There won't be any you
if you go back there.

456
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:09,520
Two minutes. I promise.

457
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:14,200
Please, just listen to me!

458
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:21,600
Sir, there's nothing you can do.

459
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:25,400
- You're dead if I leave you.
- Yes, yes, I'm dead.

460
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:27,800
- And before you go...
- I'm not going.

461
00:25:27,880 --> 00:25:31,080
Listen to me, it's important!
You can't trust her.

462
00:25:31,160 --> 00:25:32,120
- Trust who?
- River Song.

463
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:34,080
You think you know her,
but you don't.

464
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:37,280
You don't understand
who or what she is.

465
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:39,240
- Then tell me.
- I've told you more than I should.

466
00:25:39,320 --> 00:25:43,320
Now, please, you have to go,
it's your duty to your friends.

467
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:47,280
- Just tell me why she was in Stormcage.
- She killed a man.

468
00:25:47,360 --> 00:25:50,400
A good man, a hero to many.

469
00:25:50,480 --> 00:25:52,240
- Who?
- You don't want to know, sir.

470
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:53,800
You really don't.

471
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:55,200
Who did she kill?

472
00:25:55,280 --> 00:25:57,680
Sir, the Angels are coming,
you have to leave me.

473
00:25:57,760 --> 00:26:00,080
You'll die.

474
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:05,680
I will die in the knowledge that
my courage did not desert me at the end.

475
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:07,880
For that, I thank God

476
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:11,040
and bless the path
that takes you to safety.

477
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:16,760
I wish I'd known you better.

478
00:26:16,840 --> 00:26:19,040
I think, sir,

479
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:21,800
you know me at my best.

480
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:25,120
Ready?

481
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:28,840
Content.

482
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:42,280
There's a teleport! If I can get it
to work, we can beam the others here.

483
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:43,240
Where's Octavian?

484
00:26:43,320 --> 00:26:46,320
Octavian's dead. So is that teleport,
you're wasting your time.

485
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:49,000
I'm going to need your communicator.

486
00:26:52,040 --> 00:26:55,280
Hello, are you there?

487
00:26:55,360 --> 00:26:57,600
Hello?

488
00:26:57,680 --> 00:27:02,080
- Hello?
- MARCO: I'm here, I'm fine.

489
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:03,800
I'm quite close to it now.

490
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:05,400
Then come back.

491
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:07,200
Come back now, please.

492
00:27:07,280 --> 00:27:10,520
It's weird looking at it.
It feels really...

493
00:27:10,600 --> 00:27:12,440
(RADIO STATIC WHISTLES)

494
00:27:13,480 --> 00:27:16,120
Really what? Hello?

495
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:18,440
Really what?

496
00:27:18,520 --> 00:27:22,200
Hello? Hello?!

497
00:27:22,280 --> 00:27:24,080
Hello?

498
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:28,520
Please say you're there. Hello?
Hello!

499
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:34,400
DOCTOR: Amy? Amy? Is that you?

500
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:36,920
- Doctor?
- Where are you? Are the clerics with you?

501
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:40,840
They've gone. There was a light
and they walked into the light.

502
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:42,560
Doctor, they didn't even remember
each other.

503
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:44,000
No. They wouldn't.

504
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:46,320
- What is that light?
- Time running out.

505
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:48,840
Amy, I'm sorry, I made a mistake,
I should never have left you there.

506
00:27:48,920 --> 00:27:50,520
Well, what do I do now?

507
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:53,360
You come to us. Primary Flight Deck,
the other end of the forest.

508
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:55,480
I can't see! I can't open my eyes.

509
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:57,120
- Turn on the spot.
- Sorry, what?

510
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:58,720
Just do it, turn on the spot.

511
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:01,360
When the communicator sounds
like my screwdriver,

512
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:03,800
that means you're facing the right way.
Follow the sound.

513
00:28:03,880 --> 00:28:04,960
(WHIRRING)

514
00:28:05,040 --> 00:28:08,840
(WHIRRING BECOMES HIGH-PITCHED)

515
00:28:11,640 --> 00:28:14,880
You have to start moving now.

516
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:16,160
There's time energy
spilling out of that crack

517
00:28:16,240 --> 00:28:18,000
and you have to stay ahead of it.

518
00:28:18,080 --> 00:28:20,120
But the Angels, they're everywhere.

519
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:22,560
I'm sorry, I really am,
but the Angels can only kill you.

520
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:24,560
What does the time energy do?

521
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:27,840
- Just keep moving!
- Tell me!

522
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:29,920
If the time energy catches up with you,

523
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:31,520
you'll never have been born.

524
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:33,440
It will erase
every moment of your existence.

525
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:35,600
You will never have lived at all.

526
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:44,240
Now...keep your eyes shut...
and keep moving!

527
00:28:44,320 --> 00:28:47,160
- It's never going to work.
- (SHOUTS) What else have you got?

528
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:48,760
River, tell me!

529
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:05,400
(WHOOSHING, CLANGING)

530
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:08,480
- What's that?
- The Angels running from the fire.

531
00:29:08,560 --> 00:29:10,560
They came here to feed on
the time energy,

532
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:12,040
now it's going to feed on them.

533
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:15,840
Amy, listen to me, I'm sending
a bit of software to your communicator.

534
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:17,080
It's a proximity detector,

535
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:19,200
it'll beep if there's something
in your way.

536
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:21,400
You just manoeuvre
till the beeping stops.

537
00:29:21,480 --> 00:29:25,720
Because, Amy, this is important,
the forest is full of Angels.

538
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:31,240
You're going to have to walk
like you can see.

539
00:29:31,320 --> 00:29:33,000
Well, what do you mean?

540
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:34,720
Look, just keep moving.

541
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:40,560
That time energy.
What's it going to do?

542
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:42,480
Er, keep eating.

543
00:29:42,560 --> 00:29:44,920
- How do we stop it?
- Feed it.

544
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:47,280
- Feed it what?
- A big complicated space-time event,

545
00:29:47,360 --> 00:29:49,800
- should shut it up for a while.
- Like what, for instance?

546
00:29:49,880 --> 00:29:54,240
(SHOUTS) Like me, for instance!

547
00:29:57,840 --> 00:29:59,040
(HIGH-PITCHED BEEPING)

548
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:03,440
- What's that?
- It's a warning.

549
00:30:06,320 --> 00:30:08,320
There are Angels round you now.

550
00:30:13,800 --> 00:30:16,560
Amy, listen to me.
This is going to be hard, but I know...

551
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:18,600
you can do it.

552
00:30:18,680 --> 00:30:20,440
The Angels are scared and running.

553
00:30:20,520 --> 00:30:22,800
And right now they're not
that interested in you.

554
00:30:22,880 --> 00:30:26,760
They'll assume you can see them,
and their instincts will kick in.

555
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:31,200
All you've got to do is
walk like you can see.

556
00:30:31,280 --> 00:30:33,320
Just don't open your eyes.

557
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:37,000
Walk like you can see.

558
00:30:41,680 --> 00:30:44,440
You're not moving.
You have to do this.

559
00:30:46,560 --> 00:30:47,560
Now.

560
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:51,760
You have to do this!

561
00:30:51,840 --> 00:30:54,640
(COMMUNICATOR BEEPS REGULARLY)

562
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:00,360
(BEEPING SPEEDS UP)

563
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:01,880
(SHE GASPS)

564
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:03,760
(BEEPING SLOWS DOWN)

565
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:19,640
(BEEPING SPEEDS UP)

566
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:23,200
(BEEPING SLOWS DOWN)

567
00:31:34,840 --> 00:31:36,320
Argh!

568
00:31:40,360 --> 00:31:42,160
Doctor!
I can't find the communicator!

569
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:46,680
I dropped it! I can't find it, Doctor!

570
00:31:57,080 --> 00:31:58,760
Doctor...

571
00:31:58,840 --> 00:32:00,320
Doctor!

572
00:32:04,760 --> 00:32:06,600
Doctor...

573
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:24,440
Don't open your eyes.

574
00:32:24,520 --> 00:32:26,920
You're on the Flight Deck,
the Doctor's here,

575
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:29,920
I teleported you. See?

576
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:32,200
Told you I could get it working.

577
00:32:32,280 --> 00:32:33,880
River Song, I could bloody kiss you.

578
00:32:33,960 --> 00:32:36,840
Ah, well, maybe when you're older.

579
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:39,800
- (ALARM BLARES)
- What is that?

580
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:43,160
The Angels are draining the last
of the ship's power. Which means...

581
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:45,400
the shield's going to release!

582
00:33:00,440 --> 00:33:03,160
Angel Bob, I presume.

583
00:33:03,240 --> 00:33:06,720
ANGEL BOB: The time field is coming.
It will destroy our reality.

584
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:09,400
And look at you all, running away.
What can I do for you?

585
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:10,960
There is a rupture in time.

586
00:33:11,040 --> 00:33:14,240
The Angels calculate
that if you throw yourself into it,

587
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:16,200
it will close, and they will be saved.

588
00:33:16,280 --> 00:33:18,320
Yeah, yeah, could do,
could do that. But why?

589
00:33:18,400 --> 00:33:20,440
Your friends would also be saved.

590
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:22,760
- Well, there is that.
- I've travelled in time.

591
00:33:22,840 --> 00:33:24,960
I'm a complicated space-time event too,
throw me in.

592
00:33:25,040 --> 00:33:26,000
Oh, be serious!

593
00:33:26,080 --> 00:33:28,040
Compared to me, these Angels are
more complicated than you,

594
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:30,800
and it would take every one of them
to amount to me, so get a grip.

595
00:33:30,880 --> 00:33:33,640
- Doctor, I can't let you do this.
- No, seriously, get a grip.

596
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:35,760
- You're not going to die here!
- No, I mean it.

597
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:38,120
River, Amy, get a grip.

598
00:33:38,200 --> 00:33:40,280
Oh, you genius!

599
00:33:40,360 --> 00:33:44,000
Sir, the Angels need you
to sacrifice yourself now.

600
00:33:44,080 --> 00:33:47,600
Thing is, Bob, the Angels are draining
all the power from this ship,

601
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:49,760
every last bit of it.
And you know what?

602
00:33:49,840 --> 00:33:51,720
I think they've forgotten
where they're standing.

603
00:33:51,800 --> 00:33:55,640
I think they've forgotten
the gravity of the situation.

604
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:57,280
Or to put it another way, Angels...

605
00:33:57,360 --> 00:34:01,320
You hold on tight
and don't you let go for anything.

606
00:34:01,400 --> 00:34:03,160
Night-night.

607
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:51,600
- Ah, bruised everywhere.
- Me too.

608
00:34:51,680 --> 00:34:54,240
You didn't have to climb out
with your eyes shut.

609
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:56,720
Neither did you, I kept saying.

610
00:34:56,800 --> 00:35:00,040
The Angels all fell
into the time field,

611
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:03,320
the Angel in your memory
never existed.

612
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:05,360
It can't harm you now.

613
00:35:05,440 --> 00:35:07,400
Then why do I remember it at all?

614
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:10,320
Those guys on the ship
didn't remember each other.

615
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:13,200
You're a time traveller now, Amy.

616
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:16,080
Changes the way you see the universe.

617
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:18,800
For ever. Good, isn't it?

618
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:22,600
And the crack.

619
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:24,360
Is that gone too?

620
00:35:26,280 --> 00:35:27,720
Yeah.

621
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:31,400
For now.
But the explosion that caused it

622
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:33,200
is still happening...

623
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:38,280
...somewhere out there.

624
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:40,680
Somewhere in time.

625
00:35:58,720 --> 00:36:02,640
You, me...handcuffs.

626
00:36:04,720 --> 00:36:06,640
Must it always end this way?

627
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:11,560
What now?

628
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:16,160
The prison ship's in orbit,
they'll beam me up any second.

629
00:36:16,240 --> 00:36:20,080
I might have done enough
to earn a pardon this time. We'll see.

630
00:36:21,640 --> 00:36:24,240
Octavian said you killed a man.

631
00:36:25,800 --> 00:36:28,160
Yes, I did.

632
00:36:29,720 --> 00:36:31,200
A good man.

633
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:35,040
A very good man.

634
00:36:35,120 --> 00:36:37,240
The best man I've ever known.

635
00:36:40,840 --> 00:36:42,280
Who?

636
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:46,120
It's a long story, Doctor.
Can't be told, it has to be lived.

637
00:36:46,200 --> 00:36:49,520
No sneak previews.

638
00:36:49,600 --> 00:36:52,320
Well, except for this one.

639
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:54,920
You'll see me again quite soon,

640
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:58,720
when the Pandorica opens.

641
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:01,680
The Pandorica. Ha!

642
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:07,200
(WHISPERS) That's a fairy tale.

643
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:09,720
Oh, Doctor!

644
00:37:09,800 --> 00:37:11,840
Aren't we all?

645
00:37:12,920 --> 00:37:15,400
- I'll see you there.
- I look forward to it.

646
00:37:15,480 --> 00:37:17,160
I remember it well.

647
00:37:20,560 --> 00:37:23,120
Bye, River.

648
00:37:23,200 --> 00:37:24,320
See you, Amy.

649
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:25,400
(BEEPING)

650
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:27,440
Oh! I think that's my ride.

651
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:29,080
Can I trust you, River Song?

652
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:31,920
If you like.

653
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,960
But where's the fun in that?

654
00:37:54,680 --> 00:37:56,760
What are you thinking?

655
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:58,520
Time can be rewritten.

656
00:38:11,200 --> 00:38:12,680
I want to go home.

657
00:38:16,720 --> 00:38:18,200
OK.

658
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:21,840
No, not like that!

659
00:38:21,920 --> 00:38:26,400
I just... I just want
to show you something.

660
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:28,400
You're running from River.

661
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:30,960
I'm running too.

662
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:36,520
(OWL HOOTS)

663
00:38:44,720 --> 00:38:46,680
- Well!
- Yeah!

664
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:48,480
- Blimey!
- I know.

665
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:50,120
This is the same night we left, yeah?

666
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:53,200
We've been gone five minutes.

667
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:57,240
I'm getting married in the morning.

668
00:38:59,120 --> 00:39:01,040
Why did you leave it here?

669
00:39:01,160 --> 00:39:04,320
Why did I leave my engagement ring off
when I ran away with a strange man

670
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:06,000
- the night before my wedding?
- Yeah.

671
00:39:06,080 --> 00:39:08,920
You really are an alien, aren't you?

672
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:11,120
- Who's the lucky fella?
- You met him.

673
00:39:11,200 --> 00:39:15,000
Ah, the good-looking one,
or the other one?

674
00:39:15,080 --> 00:39:16,800
The other one.

675
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:19,280
- Well, he was good too.
- Thanks.

676
00:39:21,040 --> 00:39:24,240
So, do you comfort a lot of people
on the night before their wedding?

677
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:25,800
Why would you need comforting?

678
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:31,160
I nearly died. I was alone, in the dark,
and I nearly died. And it made me think...

679
00:39:31,240 --> 00:39:34,080
Well, yes, natural. I think sometimes...
Well, lots of times...

680
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:37,400
...about what I want. About who I want.

681
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:41,040
- You know what I mean?
- Yeah.

682
00:39:42,800 --> 00:39:44,560
No.

683
00:39:44,640 --> 00:39:48,760
- About who...I want.
- Oh, right, yeah.

684
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:54,640
No, still not getting it.

685
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:58,680
Doctor, in a word, in one very simple word
even you can understand...

686
00:39:58,760 --> 00:40:01,000
Uh...! You're getting married
in the morning!

687
00:40:01,080 --> 00:40:04,080
The morning's a long time away.
What are we going to do about that?

688
00:40:04,160 --> 00:40:08,120
Amy, listen to me. I'm 907 years old.
Do you understand what that means?

689
00:40:08,200 --> 00:40:10,320
- It's been a while?
- No, no, no!

690
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:13,440
I'm 907, and look at me.
I don't get older, I just change.

691
00:40:13,520 --> 00:40:15,840
You get older, I don't,
and this can't ever work.

692
00:40:15,920 --> 00:40:18,040
Oh, you are sweet, Doctor.

693
00:40:18,120 --> 00:40:21,600
But I really wasn't suggesting
anything quite so...long term.

694
00:40:25,280 --> 00:40:27,200
But you're human! You're Amy!

695
00:40:27,280 --> 00:40:30,040
You're getting married
in the morning! In the morning.

696
00:40:30,120 --> 00:40:31,800
Doctor?

697
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:36,280
It's you. It's all about you -
everything, it's about you.

698
00:40:37,320 --> 00:40:39,560
Hold that thought!

699
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:46,040
Amy Pond... Mad, impossible Amy Pond.
I don't know why, I have no idea,

700
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:49,480
but quite possibly the single
most important thing in the history

701
00:40:49,560 --> 00:40:52,400
of the universe is that I get you
sorted out right now.

702
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:54,680
That's what I've been
trying to tell you!

703
00:40:54,760 --> 00:40:56,680
Come on!

704
00:40:59,320 --> 00:41:01,360
Doctor!

705
00:41:03,600 --> 00:41:07,040
RIVER: And for those of us who can't read
the base code of the universe?

706
00:41:07,120 --> 00:41:08,960
DOCTOR: Amy's time!

